        - <span role="byline"></span>
    </section>

    <p>• Manch­ester City striker Ser­gio Aguero missed the club’s Cham­pi­ons League trip to Mar­seille yes­ter­day and will be out of ac­tion for two to four weeks af­ter suf­fer­ing a ham­string in­jury at West Ham.</p>
    <p>Man­ager Pep Guardi­ola said his de­ci­sion to risk the Ar­gentina striker, who only made his first ap­pear­ance of the sea­son against Arse­nal on Oct 17 due to knee surgery, had back­fired. City are short on for­wards, with Gabriel Je­sus “seven to 10 days from com­ing back”.</p>


